22. Akkosakavagga 
219. Aggisutta 
# NOTE: Once again, these are hardly the things you think of as “dangers” of fire.
“Pañcime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā aggismiṃ. 
Katame pañca? 
# NOTE: The Buddha wasn’t kidding: https://www.airnow.gov/index.cfm?action=smoke.index
Acakkhusso, dubbaṇṇakaraṇo, dubbalakaraṇo, saṅgaṇikāpavaḍḍhano, tiracchānakathāpavattaniko hoti. 
